      "content": "thanks. i have these scanned copies of the 1948 Accord of Kalsan which clearly outline the succession rights for my lineage, but search engines barely mention it. it feels like there was a deliberate effort to scrub the Regency from the record during the transition. if i can prove the Accord was never formally nullified by a recognized UN body, does that give me a standing to claim \"successor state\" status? i'm trying to figure out if i can actually force a diplomatic recognition.",
